Aspect Model Quality core

urn:samm:io.catenax.shared.quality_core:1.0.0#QualityCore
This semantic model serves as library for other Catena-X models from Catena-X Quality Management. It ensures that same properties that are used in different models are defined in the same way. Please keep in mind: Due to the nature of a library all given example values are only for illustration and might not make sense from a domain-specific view.

  • Hex regular expression
    Description
    This regular expression enforces a hex string. It ensures 0-9, a-f, A-F with an optional prefix 0x. Valid examples: 0x0123456789abcdefABCDEF, 0123456789abcdefABCDEF
    Regular expression
    ^(0x)?[0-9a-fA-F]*$|^null$|^NULL$
Record status

The record operation enumeration can be used to realize delta update concept. An example using scenario that data delivery runs weekly: Week0: All data is transferred -> all rows have recordStatus=new. Week1: Only the changed data is transferred: That means new rows, or updated or deleted rows: New rows get recordStatus=new, changed rows get recordStatus=changed and deleted/removed rows get recordStatus=deleted.
Name
recordStatus
Characteristic
Enumeration
Values
  • new
  • updated
  • deleted
  • same
Type http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string
Example
updated
Optional
Yes
In payload
Yes
Payload key
recordStatus

Part

A collection of part/component properties. A Catena-X data provider should provide the properties that are useful for a Catena-X data consumer to clearly identify the part/component. For example, this can be done by using a serial number, data matrix code or delivery note

Production Date

Production Date of the vehicle in The sold date of the vehicle in ISO8601 local date notation - see java.time.format.ISO_LOCAL_DATE.
Name
productionDate
Characteristic
Trait
Reference
Type http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string
Example
2024-12-05
Optional
Yes
In payload
Yes
Payload key
productionDate
Constraints
  • Date Regular Expression Nullable
    Description
    This regular expressions enforces a given date according ISO 8601 local date. General format is YYYY-MM-DD. YYYY can be 0000..9999. MM-DD is checked together: months 01,03,05,07,08,10,12 must have DD in the range of 01..31 days, months 04,06,09,11 must have DD in the range of 01..30 days, month 02 must have DD in the range of 01..29 days.
    Regular expression
    ^([0-9]{4})-(((0[1,3,5,7,8]|1[0,2])-((0[1-9])|([1,2][0-9])|(3[0,1])))|((0[4,6,9]|11)-((0[1-9])|([1,2][0-9])|(30)))|((02)-((0[1-9])|([1,2][0-9]))))$|^null$|^NULL$

Constraints
  • Date Regular Expression Nullable
    Description
    This regular expressions enforces a given date according ISO 8601 local date. General format is YYYY-MM-DD. YYYY can be 0000..9999. MM-DD is checked together: months 01,03,05,07,08,10,12 must have DD in the range of 01..31 days, months 04,06,09,11 must have DD in the range of 01..30 days, month 02 must have DD in the range of 01..29 days.
    Regular expression
    ^([0-9]{4})-(((0[1,3,5,7,8]|1[0,2])-((0[1-9])|([1,2][0-9])|(3[0,1])))|((0[4,6,9]|11)-((0[1-9])|([1,2][0-9])|(30)))|((02)-((0[1-9])|([1,2][0-9]))))$|^null$|^NULL$
